    "verified": true,
    "text": "This is the most bizzare case.\n\n2 FP were reported.\n\nThis first FP is instance (Enter Parking Lot, Raise Exit Barrier) because the elements are not related, and \"Raise Exit Barrier\" is included by \"Exit Parking Lot\" \n\nThe second FP is instance (Exit Parking Lot, Validate Payment Details) because the elements are not related, and \"Validate Payment Details\" is included by \"Process Payment\".\n\n4 FN were reported.\n\nThe first FN is missed instance (Enter Parking Lot, Open Entry Gate), which is part of instance group {(Enter Parking Lot, Scan Entry Ticket), (Enter Parking Lot, Open Entry Gate)}\n\nThe second FN is missed instance (Exit Parking Lot, Calculate Parking Fee), which is part of instance group {(Exit Parking Lot, Calculate Parking Fee), (Exit Parking Lot, Raise Exit Barrier)}\n\nThe third FN is missed instance (Exit Parking Lot, Raise Exit Barrier), which is part of instance group {(Exit Parking Lot, Calculate Parking Fee), (Exit Parking Lot, Raise Exit Barrier)}\n\nThe fourth FN is missed instance (Process Payment, Validate Payment Details) which is a standard FD-include. Note that \"Process Payment\" is associated with two actors \"Driver\" and \"Payment Gateway\". Perhaps this instance was missed because the base use case was associated with multiple actors.\n\n1 instance correctly predicted (Enter Parking Lot, Scan Entry Ticket)  ",
    "updated_at": "2026-05-27T16:04:07.058668"
  },
